entries.femaleVariant: Tough to say... all happened in a blink.
Know one thing for sure – she was terrified.
I appreciate the candor. It seems it's all for one and one for all if we're to survive.
Provided we both survive this ordeal.
Well... We didn't account for this.
I'm dying. Piss on the details.
Got an... experimental Arasaka biochip in my brain. It's killin' me, literally. So Mi says she might have a solution.
Never mind the tech details. Songbird claims she can help.
Wait – you're talking about the Relic.
The secretive tech someone stole from Arasaka. On the day Saburo lost his battle with mortality, no less.
Honest truth is... I'm dyin'. 'Cause of the Relic.
Like she had her worst fears boxed up, and... that box popped open.
Funny how she has her own street in Night City of all places.
Bullheaded Betty – that's what we called her. Reelected nine times, you believe it? She must've had her ass welded to that seat.
I just hope this won't be a dead end.
Hold up, V. Let's pause. Think for a sec.
Stopping's not a good idea. We get pinned down, we're ground synthbeef.
Exactly. But So Mi can guide us out of this death trap. Call her, please.
Just felt my second wind arrive.
Waste of time... All these tunnels are unfinished.
Huh, our stop. On the right, see it?
Mhh. I'm going to smell musty for a week.
Come on, don't be shy. Mutual trust has gotten us this far.
So that's your deal... I had a feeling you weren't in this for the money.
Ugh, it's a freight car. You can only open it from the outside.
Got a hatch here. Could we jump, maybe?
Somethin' was off for sure. Could say she got hit with a daemon, maybe tripped a defense protocol in the Chimera's ICE…
Lost control of the mech, I think.
All I know she lost control of the spidermech, all of a sudden. Maybe of herself, too.
So Mi's had occasional... off moments lately. Temporary slumps.
But I'm sure she's headed where we're headed, the same destination she gave us. It's the reasonable thing to do.
Y'know, no netrun comes without a burn risk…
Hot as Satan's balls in here. Should plug that.
Security cams might've caught glimpses of us. Should we wipe the memory, just in case?
A maintenance tunnel... We could try to squeeze through.
But who knows. Mh, whole thing was a clusterfuck.
entries.maleVariant: Eh, but who knows. Whole thing was a clusterfuck.

entries.femaleVariant: Let me lend you a hand.
Hansen's a military man. He loves control and hates blind spots.
Can you try calling So Mi again?
What happened back there? With So Mi.
OK. Gonna give it a shot.
entries.maleVariant: OK, gonna give it a shot.

entries.femaleVariant: Well? What's there to think about?
She was simultaneously wrestling down the Chimera, monitoring the situation and staying in touch with you.
Mhm. If Songbird was a cookie-cutter 'runner. Both know she's not, though.
You don't know or you'd rather not say?
I could really use some help here.
A little help? We're wastin' time.
If you're lookin' for somethin', at least make it quick.
One's clearly favored, gets more traffic.
entries.maleVariant: One's clearly favored, gets lots more traffic.

entries.femaleVariant: Question is, what kind of traffic? The kind we need to avoid?
My money's on drifters. Sewers and old tunnels make for warm havens on cold nights.
Other option's mostly rubble, no fresh tracks... Not sure I'd call that a good sign, though.
That said, places like this, never can be completely sure who you'll run into.
You lead. You'll make a sound choice, I know that.
What's the matter? Are you hurt?
V, please... I have a highly honed nose for bullshit.
Yeah, could say that. Old wound.
One that literally has you on the floor.
Well, you didn't hightail it out and away when the shit got neck-deep.
V, how concerned should I be?
I know it's a sensitive subject, V, but c'mon – cards on the table.
So that's how she could reach you. It also goes a long way towards explaining the nature of your deal.
Riiight, reasonable. Girl's gonna have a helluva hangover… if she wakes up.
Curb the enthusiasm, kid. Never know, could need me.
Felt like I was under water… leagues down. Tried to surface, but this suffocating, suckin' sound pulled me back in.
Then, when she lost control of the… Chimera... the water turned into fuckin' boilin' tar.
Sounds unsettling, to say the least.
Seems like the sitch spiralled outta control.
entries.maleVariant: Seems the sitch spiralled outta control.

entries.femaleVariant: For me, yeah. But for her...?
Unamused. Not the time for jokes, Johnny.
'Cause I wound up at the same rave she went to.
Long time no see, Johnny. You all good?
Me? Pfft. Should be asking about Songbird.
Though actually, could've been a straight overload… Seen 'runners caught in those. Shit's ugly.
We're heading southwest now. It feels like we're circling back.
Uh-huh. Song mentioned an abandoned building, place to lie low. No heat sig, so should be "relatively safe."
entries.maleVariant: Yeah. Song mentioned an abandoned building, place to lie low. No heat sig, should be "relatively safe."

entries.femaleVariant: I pray you're right, So Mi.
No answer, huh? Guess you got me and only me.
Songbird said to keep to the tunnels all the way to Elizabeth Kress Street.
Songbird – the most competent netrunner I can think of, let alone know. She'll help, I'll make sure of it…
Ah, a Relic...? Interesting. So Mi's choice was less random than I thought. It should've been obvious.
